  <scopecontent id="aspace_932c0a8cd508c91cf583492016714fd1">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The Ost Family Papers (dated 1948-2014) consist of materials created and collected by Milton and Ruth Ost documenting their personal lives and political engagements. Materials in this collection include copies of Milton's writings, including a script for <emph render="italic">The Warsaw Ghetto Uprising</emph>; documents from Milton's memorial service at Riverside Memorial Chapel; and photographs from Steve Nelson's 72nd birthday celebration, where he was honored at the Veterans of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade Luncheon. The collection also includes correspondence, including correspondence between Ruth and her sister Faith Bonosky, the wife of Philip Bonosky. Ruth and Faith's letters help document the Bonosky's family life, including the time period that the Bonoskys lived in the USSR. Other correspondents include Henry Foner, Steve Nelson, and friends and family expressing their condolences following Milton's death. Other materials include ephemera and writings by Bill Mardo, the sports writer for the <emph render="italic">Daily Worker</emph>, Ruth's life partner after Milton's death.</p>  </scopecontent>
